151
00:09:21,820 --> 00:09:24,500
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>And with a cliff to your left,</i></font>

152
00:09:24,500 --> 00:09:28,410
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>you subconsciously drift to the 
rightmost edge of the jumping-off point.</i></font>

153
00:09:28,760 --> 00:09:33,260
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>But Kanata went as far left as he could.</i></font>

154
00:09:33,620 --> 00:09:38,090
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Where does such a gentle-looking dude 
get the balls for this stuff?</font>

155
00:09:39,300 --> 00:09:42,290
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>{\an8}The traffic lights mark 
the start of Sector 3.</i></font>

156
00:09:42,760 --> 00:09:45,910
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>{\an8}Up to this point, he's matching the time
 of Sawatari in the 4.</i></font>

157
00:09:46,360 --> 00:09:50,690
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>{\an8}The upcoming bumpy stretch has tested 
the footwork of many an MFG racer.</i></font>

158
00:09:51,100 --> 00:09:53,900
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>{\an8}But Katagiri Kanata shows no hesitation.</i></font>

159
00:09:58,260 --> 00:10:02,520
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>{\an8}While the bumps affect his racing line, 
he compensates with incredible smoothness.</i></font>

160
00:10:02,520 --> 00:10:04,660
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>{\an8}This driver is in total control of his car.</i></font>

161
00:10:04,970 --> 00:10:08,250
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">What do you think, Shun? 
About Kanata's driving.</font>

162
00:10:08,250 --> 00:10:10,610
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">What do you mean? It's the same as usual.</font>

163
00:10:10,610 --> 00:10:13,140
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Or maybe even a little better?</font>

164
00:10:13,140 --> 00:10:14,420
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">That's what I thought.</font>

165
00:10:14,710 --> 00:10:18,550
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">By weaponizing the aero, 
the 86 can fight harder.</font>

166
00:10:18,550 --> 00:10:20,170
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">And Kanata can feel that.</font>

167
00:10:20,440 --> 00:10:22,680
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">But despite that, 
since entering Sector 3,</font>

168
00:10:22,680 --> 00:10:25,780
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">he's fallen behind the 4 car's pace.</font>

169
00:10:27,260 --> 00:10:30,810
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">At this late stage, there's a slight 
difference in their times.</font>

170
00:10:31,300 --> 00:10:33,950
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>{\an8}He still has an attention flag, 
but in spite of that,</i></font>

171
00:10:33,950 --> 00:10:37,730
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>{\an8}the 4 car is now ahead 
by three-hundredths of a second!</i></font>

172
00:10:38,360 --> 00:10:42,400
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>{\an8}There's not much of the lap left. 
As he approaches the finish line...</i></font>

173
00:10:42,900 --> 00:10:47,740
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Y'know, in all the other races, 
whenever Kanata had any issues,</font>

174
00:10:47,960 --> 00:10:50,130
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">it was due to the car
 being underpowered,</font>

175
00:10:50,130 --> 00:10:53,120
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">causing him to fall behind 
the competition as a result.</font>

176
00:10:53,660 --> 00:10:58,020
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">But I don't think that's why Sawatari
 has the edge right now.</font>

177
00:10:58,020 --> 00:11:03,970
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">I don't think I've seen a situation 
where he's simply been outperformed.</font>

178
00:11:04,300 --> 00:11:07,060
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Well, this sport is still a
 competition between humans.</font>

179
00:11:07,060 --> 00:11:10,360
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">At the highest levels, 
athletes outperform each other</font>

180
00:11:10,360 --> 00:11:13,940
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">from one moment to the next 
due to slight changes in conditions.</font>

181
00:11:14,530 --> 00:11:16,780
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Experience and stuff also plays a role.</font>

182
00:11:17,220 --> 00:11:20,660
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Maybe it boils down to the fact 
Sawatari has been here twice before</font>

183
00:11:20,660 --> 00:11:24,030
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">whereas this is Kanata's first time
 tackling this course.</font>

184
00:11:27,820 --> 00:11:30,640
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>{\an8}The 86 is nearly at the finish line...</i></font>

185
00:11:30,640 --> 00:11:31,740
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>{\an8}And...</i></font>

186
00:11:31,740 --> 00:11:33,080
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>{\an8}There it is!</i></font>

187
00:11:33,390 --> 00:11:36,380
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>{\an8}He wasn't able to break 
the new course record.</i></font>

188
00:11:36,380 --> 00:11:39,430
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>{\an8}He qualifies in second provisionally.</i></font>

189
00:11:39,850 --> 00:11:44,470
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>{\an8}He was a scant 0.32 seconds 
behind Sawatari in the 4 car.</i></font>

190
00:11:44,890 --> 00:11:48,410
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>{\an8}And I'm sure I don't need to explain
 how incredible that is.</i></font>

191
00:11:50,610 --> 00:11:51,950
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>{\an8}MF Ghost.</i></font>

192
00:11:56,730 --> 00:11:57,950
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>{\an8}MF Ghost.</i></font>

193
00:12:03,990 --> 00:12:06,110
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>I don't get Sawatari and Katagiri.</i></font>

194
00:12:06,110 --> 00:12:10,990
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>However far you take this jump, 
it doesn't shave that much off your time.</i></font>

195
00:12:12,030 --> 00:12:13,460
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>Are they stupid?</i></font>

196
00:12:14,590 --> 00:12:18,880
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">On top of the prize money, 
MFG has this bonus system.</font>

197
00:12:19,090 --> 00:12:22,130
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">You get the cash for it in a lump sum
 at the end of the season.</font>

198
00:12:22,360 --> 00:12:25,400
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">It's one million yen per overtake.</font>

199
00:12:25,400 --> 00:12:28,680
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">So you're looking at a ten million yen
 bonus just from Peninsula.</font>

200
00:12:28,910 --> 00:12:29,900
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><font face="Times New Roman">Really?</font></font>

201
00:12:29,900 --> 00:12:34,140
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">You didn't know? Well, putting 
the whole money thing aside...</font>

202
00:12:34,700 --> 00:12:38,500
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Overtaking ten people in a single race
 just doesn't happen. Not usually.</font>

203
00:12:38,500 --> 00:12:42,570
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Hell, last year, there were maybe ten overtakes
 per race across the whole field.</font>

204
00:12:43,030 --> 00:12:48,260
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">I figure I oughta ask. What goes on
 in your head when you're driving?</font>

205
00:12:48,260 --> 00:12:50,860
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Huh? What do I think about?</font>

206
00:12:52,840 --> 00:12:54,450
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">It's hard to say.</font>

207
00:12:54,780 --> 00:12:57,820
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">My body usually reacts reflexively
 before I have time to think.</font>

208
00:12:57,820 --> 00:13:01,840
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Especially when overtaking someone. 
If I'm feeling good, it's automatic.</font>

209
00:13:02,480 --> 00:13:06,130
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">In the first two races, 
I wasn't pulling moves off too well.</font>

210
00:13:06,130 --> 00:13:10,140
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">I must've gotten too in my own head. 
And I was in a bit of a slump.</font>

211
00:13:10,470 --> 00:13:14,100
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>That was you in a </i>slump<i>? Holy crap.</i></font>

212
00:13:14,100 --> 00:13:17,040
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">The change came during the third race.</font>

213
00:13:17,040 --> 00:13:19,410
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">I got the feel for it back
 at a good moment.</font>

214
00:13:19,410 --> 00:13:23,860
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">And I can't explain it very well, but my body 
started moving on its own again.</font>

215
00:13:23,860 --> 00:13:25,790
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>Not thinking, huh?</i></font>

216
00:13:26,170 --> 00:13:29,360
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>That kinda thing is hard for 
a normal guy like me to grasp.</i></font>

217
00:13:29,360 --> 00:13:33,070
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>{\an8}Customer 172, your food is ready.</i></font>

218
00:13:33,070 --> 00:13:34,300
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">That's ours.</font>

219
00:13:35,750 --> 00:13:38,120
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Wow. This looks delicious.</font>

220
00:13:38,350 --> 00:13:41,730
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Eat your fill, all right? It's my treat.</font>

221
00:13:47,020 --> 00:13:48,030
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Miss Greene.</font>

222
00:13:48,720 --> 00:13:52,360
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">There's a special lounge.
You should rest up there.</font>

223
00:13:52,740 --> 00:13:54,350
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Thank you, Hayato.</font>

224
00:13:54,540 --> 00:13:56,980
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">I'm fully prepared, 
and looking forward to this.</font>

225
00:13:57,750 --> 00:14:00,860
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">But I won't go all out. 
Better to take it easy.</font>

226
00:14:01,340 --> 00:14:04,780
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>It's only qualifying. 
Making the top five should suffice.</i></font>

227
00:14:05,990 --> 00:14:09,110
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Aw, man. Maezono-san, 
did you see that chick?</font>

228
00:14:09,460 --> 00:14:14,910
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">There was this gorgeous woman in
the special lounge. A blonde foreigner.</font>

229
00:14:14,910 --> 00:14:18,500
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">I figured I'd shoot my shot
 and went over to talk to her,</font>

230
00:14:18,810 --> 00:14:21,180
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">but she didn't know a lick of Japanese</font>

231
00:14:21,180 --> 00:14:23,960
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">and straight up ignored me.
Talk about crash and burn.</font>

232
00:14:24,160 --> 00:14:25,530
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Akaba-kun.</font>

233
00:14:26,050 --> 00:14:29,970
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">That's the first thing out of your mouth
 on the morning of your qualifying run?</font>

234
00:14:30,280 --> 00:14:35,910
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Most people would mention the insane laps
of Sawatari Koki and Katagiri Kanata.</font>

235
00:14:35,910 --> 00:14:40,740
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">That's just the thing. She was so hot,
 I forgot all about that stuff.</font>

236
00:14:40,740 --> 00:14:43,590
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Your brain works in 
very interesting ways.</font>

237
00:14:45,560 --> 00:14:50,220
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>{\an8}Five, four, three, two, one...</i></font>

238
00:14:52,550 --> 00:14:55,620
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>{\an8}And off goes last year's 
polesitter, Akaba Kaito.</i></font>

239
00:14:55,870 --> 00:15:00,450
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>{\an8}A fiery driver with a distinct advantage
 on high-speed courses, he bolts away!</i></font>

240
00:15:01,910 --> 00:15:04,040
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>I've got a shot at winning Double Lane.</i></font>

241
00:15:04,500 --> 00:15:09,340
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>And on my pride in the number 2 on 
this car, I'm gonna prove to the fans...</i></font>

242
00:15:09,760 --> 00:15:11,990
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>that I'm more than just a womanizer.</i></font>

243
00:15:12,430 --> 00:15:14,710
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>This is where Akaba Kaito strikes back.</i></font>

244
00:15:15,430 --> 00:15:21,560
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Makes sense the Ferrari with its 700 HP
 would shine on the high-speed sections.</font>

245
00:15:21,980 --> 00:15:26,440
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Agreed. Although it may 
have <i>too</i> much power.</font>

246
00:15:26,770 --> 00:15:31,110
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">When driving, you end up dealing with 
lateral Gs for longer than you'd think.</font>

247
00:15:31,110 --> 00:15:34,700
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">That limits the amount of time
 you can go all out.</font>

248
00:15:35,810 --> 00:15:37,990
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Whoops. Look at that rear end wobble.</font>

249
00:15:37,990 --> 00:15:41,830
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">That was definitely a bit loose. 
It cost him some time.</font>

250
00:15:42,340 --> 00:15:45,840
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>{\an8}The 2 car looks shaky 
coming out of that corner.</i></font>

251
00:15:45,840 --> 00:15:50,590
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>{\an8}But he's already ahead 
of his time from last year.</i></font>

252
00:15:50,870 --> 00:15:53,090
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>{\an8}Akaba Kaito's making it look easy.</i></font>

253
00:15:53,300 --> 00:15:56,760
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>{\an8}The Ferrari music is echoing
across the waters of Sagami Bay.</i></font>

254
00:16:01,550 --> 00:16:05,270
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>I'm starting to have doubts 
about my own performance.</i></font>

255
00:16:05,470 --> 00:16:10,370
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>One of the younger drivers 
is stirring something in me.</i></font>

256
00:16:11,280 --> 00:16:13,030
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>Katagiri Kanata.</i></font>

257
00:16:13,030 --> 00:16:15,900
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>I can't understand how he's so fast.</i></font>

258
00:16:15,900 --> 00:16:20,140
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>And I can't accept the fact I'm having 
trouble explaining the physics of it.</i></font>

259
00:16:20,810 --> 00:16:24,600
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>{\an8}Maezono Kazuhiro is 
MFG's most logical driver.</i></font>

260
00:16:24,600 --> 00:16:28,900
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>{\an8}With a high IQ and scientific brain, 
he seeks to conquer Double Lane.</i></font>

261
00:16:30,890 --> 00:16:33,340
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>Thanks for tuning in
 to day six of qualifying.</i></font>

262
00:16:33,340 --> 00:16:36,560
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>I'd like everyone 
to pay special attention</i></font>

